title: Rails West (Train History).pdf
description:
Rails West
Superior Publishing Company | 1960 | English | 200 pages | PDF | 30 MB

The past century saw steam locomotives and brave little trains conquer the frontier and become a powerful influence in every American's life. Then the railroad age suddenly faded out to leave only memories and misty eyes.
In his three splendid books, George Abdill has caught the pioneer spirit and presents the finest, most comprehensive collection of early steam railroads ever put between book covers. Coupled to this vast dramatic show are human interest tales of the men who sought adventure and became legends in the push of steam and steel
